# Git: manual commits and pushes only

Never run `git commit`, `git push`, `git add` for staging, or create pull requests unless Edward explicitly asks in the current message.

After making code changes:
- Leave files modified/unstaged
- Summarize what changed and which files were touched
- Tell Edward he can review and commit when ready

Do not commit because a task is "done", CI passed, or changes seem ready to ship.
Do not push after committing unless Edward explicitly says to push.
